featured.title: UTM Ascends: Treetop Trekking Adventure
featured.description: Zip, climb, and conquer the canopy! Navigate through a treetop obstacle course filled with ziplines, rope bridges, and forest views — perfect for thrill-seekers and beginners alike.

featured.title: Move & Learn Series: Latin American Heritage Month
UTM Walks: Fall Colours and Salmon Migration
featured.description: (Faciliated by The Riverwood Conservancy, at Erindale Park)Explore the beautiful Erindale Park, a short walk from the UTM campus. On this guided walk, we'll soak in the blazing fall colours of Erindale's forest canopy, observing many aspects of the changing season. Fall is also the time of the annual salmon migration. We'll walk along the Credit River in the park, and learn more about the incredible salmon as they take their last leg of the journey from Lake Ontario all the way up the Credit River to spawn the next generation. This walk will be guided by nature guides from The Riverwood Conservancy.

featured.title: Move & Learn Series: World Mental Health Day
UTM Goes Forestbathing: Nature Immersion Adventure - In Celebration of World Mental Health Day
featured.description: (Faciliated by The Riverwood Conservancy)Join us for a mindful experience at Riverwood and deepen your relationship with nature. Forest bathing is inspired by the Japanese practice of Shinrin-yoku, which gives you the chance to reconnect with nature.

featured.title: UTM Dances: Learn Bhangra with Sifat Canada
featured.description: Experience the joy and energy of Bhangra, a traditional folk dance from Punjab, India known for its vibrant and rhythmic movements! Register today for any of our four 30-minute workshops where we'll break down basic Bhangra moves and combine them into a dynamic routine set to upbeat music. Open to all UTM students. No prior experience needed. Join us for a day of energy and movement, while boosting your wellness in an exciting way! Register for any one of the following four back-to-back introductory classes.

featured.title: Trick-or-Trek: The RAWC's Spooktacular Scavenger Hunt
featured.description: Get ready to embark on a thrilling adventure across campus as you "trick or treat" at nine Halloween monster-themed stations. At each stop, you'll engage in a fun physical or wellness activity, earning both a treat and a sticker for your bingo card! From terrifying exercise challenges to creepy carnival games and enchanted crafts, there’s a little something for everyone! Gather your friends, collect your goodies, and see if you can complete the bingo card for a chance at even more surprises!

featured.title: MoveU Refresh & Recharge: Tri-Campus Hart House Farm Trip
featured.description: Escape the books with a daytrip to experience caving, cider making, archery, s'mores and more! This getaway is all about having fun, making friends, and enjoying nature's beauty with peers from across all three UofT campuses. Bus transportation is included. Buses will depart UTM at 9:15 AM and return to campus by 6 PM.

featured.title: UTM Walks: Campus Birdwatching
featured.description: Join us for a birdwatching walk led by UTM Biology Professor Sanja Hinic-Frlog! Explore campus trails and observe local birdlife while connecting with other UTM students, no experience or equipment required.Meet at RAWC Lobby, we depart no later than 10 minutes past the hour.

featured.title: UTM Rides: Horseback Riding Adventure
featured.description: Saddle up and ride! Take in the beauty of nature on horseback with this scenic trail ride experience. No prior riding experience needed — just a love of the outdoors.

announcements.title: Residence Night Sundays (6:00 PM - 9:00 PM)
announcements.body:
Every Sunday, residence students have additional access hours at the RAWC from 6:00 PM - 9:00 PM. Students can take advantage of the extra hours by working out at the Fitness Centre, jump in Fun Swim at the Pool or participate in sports programs in Gym A/B.
Weekly schedule can be found in [**our online calendar**](https://www.utm.utoronto.ca/athletics/schedule).
